h1. Sweeper, a HDFS browser

h2. USAGE

@java -jar target/metrics.sweeper-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar@

You can configure the namenode url via @sweeper.hadoop.namenode.url@:

@java  -Dsweeper.hadoop.namenode.url=hdfs://namenode.mycompany.com:9000 -jar target/metrics.sweeper-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar@

You can configure the credentials via @sweeper.hadoop.ugi@ (make sure to escape the coma):

@java -Dsweeper.hadoop.ugi='hadoop-user\,hadoop-group' -jar target/metrics.sweeper-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar@

By default, the browser will look at the entire cluster. You can specify a specific path via @sweeper.hadoop.path@:

@java -Dsweeper.hadoop.path=/user/pierre -jar target/metrics.sweeper-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar@

By default, files and directories size are shown (taking into account the replication factor). To show the number of files, use @sweeper.content_summary=NUMBER_OF_FILES@:

@java -Dsweeper.content_summary=NUMBER_OF_FILES -jar target/metrics.sweeper-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar@

h2. BUILD

@mvn assembly:assembly@

